titles.title: A concurrent resolution to correct technical errors in the enrollment of the bill (H.R. 2403), and for other purposes.

vote.text: Submitted in the Senate, considered, and agreed to without amendment by Voice Vote.

action.text: Message on Senate action sent to the House.
Mr. Hoyer asked unanimous consent to take from the Speaker's table and consider.
An objection was heard to the unanimous consent request to consider the measure.
Mr. Hoyer asked unanimous consent to take from the Speaker's table and consider.

vote.text: On agreeing to the resolution Agreed to without objection.

action.text: Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.

bill.summary: 10/21/1993--Introduced. Makes technical corrections in the enrollment of H.R. 2403 (Department of the Treasury, United States Postal Service, the Executive Office of the President, and certain independent agencies appropriations).
